<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880919-0145 </DOCNO><HL> Galveston-Houston Offer </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GHX </CO><IN> BBK </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Galveston-Houston Co. said it started an offer to buy back its stock from holders of fewer than 100 shares.    The company, which makes and markets products for the mining, construction and energy industries, said it would pay $1.75 a share and assume all brokerage costs for shares tendered under the offer. The offer, designed to reduce the company's shareholder service costs, expires Oct. 31, Galveston-Houston said.    As of June 30, Galveston-Houston had 11,020,505 shares outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>